Content:
I really like the presentation of the problems. I hope this is developed much further. It could, however, benefit a lot by having separate quizzes at different levels, and moving the edge-cases and browser-specific questions into their own quizzes. I also question the value of questions that are intentionally meant to trick you.<p>Some of these questions, by their nature of being browser-specific, are time sensitive since no versions are specified. And I&#x27;d have to double-check all of these answers because I found at least one which is wrong:<p><pre><code>    window.onresize = function(){window.location.reload()}
</code></pre>
Definitely reloads the page in Chrome 27 (and the current Canary, 29).
